<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880718-0029 </DOCNO><HL> New Securities Issues </HL><SO> </SO><CO> EUROP SB MER </CO><IN> BON FIN BNK REL CON </IN><TEXT>      The following were among Friday's offerings and pricings in the U.S. and non-U.S. capital markets, with terms and syndicate manager, as compiled by Dow Jones Capital Markets Report:                          MORTGAGES   Salomon Brothers Inc. -- An issue of CMO Trust 45 Remic mortgage securities has been increased to $300 million from $200 million. The issue, backed by Freddie Mac 9% securities, was freed to trade Thursday afternoon after selling out. The sizes of the six classes of the issue, by a trust established by Salomon Brothers, were increased by 50%.                         ASSET-BACKED   Merrill Lynch Asset-Backed Corp. -- $524.6 million of notes backed by automobile receivables with an 8.5% coupon rate were sold through Merrill Lynch Capital Markets. The issue is backed by loans purchased from First Nationwide Bank. Ford Motor Credit Co. is the servicer of the contracts. The offering, the first by the company, is series 1988A. It has a final maturity of June 25, 1991. Merrill Lynch Asset-Backed is a wholly owned, limited purpose subsidiary of Merrill Lynch Mortgage Capital Inc. The subsidiary was established to purchase consumer receivables from originators and issue collateralized debt securities. The notes are expected to be rated triple-A by Moody's Investors Service Inc.                              EUROBONDS   Hokuriku Bank Ltd. (Japan) -- $100 million of convertible bonds due March 31, 2003, indicating a semiannual coupon of 3 1/8% at par, via Hokuriku Finance and Yamaichi International (Europe) Ltd. Exercisable Aug. 16, 1988, to March 12, 2003, at expected premium of 5% when terms are fixed Friday. Call from March 31, 1991, at 104, declining by 1/2 point a year to par, but not before March 31, 1993, unless share price exceeds 150% of conversion price for 30 trading days.   ABN International Financial Services Co. (Dutch parent) -- 150 million Swiss francs of 4 1/4% bonds due Aug. 15, 1993, priced at 100 1/4 to yield 4.194%, via Swiss Bank Corp. Guaranteed by parent, Algemene-Bank Nederland NV. Public subscription ends Aug. 4.   Banco di Roma (Italy) -- 100 million Swiss francs of 4 1/4% notes due August 1995, priced at 100 1/4 to yield 4.46% at issue price, via Union Bank of Switzerland.   Hokuriku Bank -- 100 million Swiss francs of convertible notes due Sept. 30, 1993, indicating 1/2% coupon at par, via Swiss Bank. Call from March 31, 1991, at 102 1/2, declining by  1/2 point semiannually. Acceleration clause from Sept. 30, 1989, at 104, declining by 1/2 semiannually. Exercisable Aug. 16, 1988, to Sept. 13, 1993, at an indicated premium of 5% above the share close when terms are fixed Thursday.   PKbanken (Sweden) -- 5 billion yen of floating-rate notes due Aug. 15, 1992, paying two basis points over Japanese long-term prime rate at 101 5/8 with redemption linked to Nikkei 225 stock index, via Nippon Credit International Ltd. Call and put options Aug. 15, 1991, based on Nikkei 225 index.</TEXT></DOC>